            <note xml:id="foot.f5">CD discussed the dispersal of seeds by birds in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6014.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Origin</hi></ref>, pp. 356–65, in the context of geographical distribution; he mentioned colourful seeds in relation to the idea of beauty in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6017.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> 4th ed.</ref>, p. 240.</note>
